There are two forms of apterous females in this species: strongly pigmented and poorly pigmented (
Figures 1– 2
).

Color in macerated specimens: Head and ANT I–III dark brown, ANT IV–IV light brown or dusky; thorax dark or black; fore femora dusky with brown apices, mid and hind femora brown with pale bases; apices of tibiae and tarsi brown; SIPH and cauda brown; ABD TERG I–VI often with spinopleural bars, sometimes with spinal bars; ABD TERG II–IV with marginal sclerites; presiphuncular and postsiphuncular sclerites developed; ABD TERG VII–VIII with dark bands (
Fig. 3
).
